<div i18n:domain="quotationtool">
  
  <h1 i18n:translate="">Workflow</h1>

  <p i18n:translate="workflow-history-description">
    Adding, changing, removing items to the database is controled by
    workflow processes, that let the site's editors decide whether an
    item, some user contributes, will be published or not, whether it
    needs changes, whether it will be removed etc. Contributions,
    requests for change or removal and the decisions of the editors
    make the item's workflow history.
  </p>

  <tal:block condition="view/notations">
  <h2 i18n:translate="">Workflow History (reversed order)</h2>
  <div class="workflow-history">
    <div tal:repeat="notation view/notations" 
	 tal:content="structure notation/@@details">
    </div>
  </div>
  </tal:block>

  <h2 i18n:translate="">Current Work Items</h2>

  <div tal:replace="structure view/renderTable"/>

</div>
